(9853, '1CAF3425-F2E2-4046-8640-A14ECD897270', 'Our travel agent Claude is helping us…  Sure, I''d be happy to help you plan a 9-day trip to Greece with a focus on the island of Naxos for you and your 7-year-old daughter. Here''s a suggested itinerary:  **Day 1-2: Athens** - Arrive in Athens and spend the first two days exploring the city''s top sights: - Visit the Acropolis and the Acropolis Museum - Wander through the Plaka neighborhood  - Check out the Acropolis Museum - Take a food tour to sample traditional Greek cuisine  **Days 3-8: Naxos** - Take a ferry from Athens to the island of Naxos (approx. 2.5 hour ride) - Spend the majority of your trip, 6 days, on Naxos. Some activities to consider:  - Explore the Old Town of Naxos and the iconic Portara (ancient Greek temple gateway) - Visit the mountain village of Apiranthos, known for its traditional architecture - Go hiking in the island''s interior to see the scenic mountains and valleys - Spend time at the beautiful beaches of Plaka, Agia Anna, and Agios Prokopios - Take a boat tour to small islands and inlets around Naxos - Visit the Archaeological Museum to learn about the island''s history - Let your daughter enjoy watersports like swimming, snorkeling, or paddleboarding - Check out the local festivals and events if you visit during a feast day  **Day 9: Return to Athens** - Spend your final day back in Athens before departing.  Some additional tips: - Consider renting a car on Naxos to have more flexibility in exploring the island. - Look into family-friendly hotels and villas, some with pools, to make the most of your beach time. - Build in some downtime for your daughter to recharge between activities. - Check event calendars for any special festivals or celebrations happening during your visit.  Let me know if you need any other suggestions as you finalize your Greece itinerary! I''m happy to provide more details.', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2024-04-15T12:21:12.794000'),
(9464, '677B4F4E-DAAB-4857-872F-F6DA43130704', 'If you''d like to avoid the intense heat of Athens in late June, here are some alternative recommendations for your Greece trip:  1. Focus more time on the Greek Islands: - Spend extra days on Naxos, allowing your daughter to enjoy the beaches, watersports, and leisurely island lifestyle. - Consider adding another island like Paros, Antiparos, or Amorgos to your itinerary. These smaller, less crowded islands can be great for families.  2. Visit the Peloponnese Peninsula: - Explore historic sites like Ancient Olympia, the birthplace of the Olympic Games. - Spend time in coastal towns like Nafplio, with its Venetian old town and seaside promenade. - Hike through the beautiful Mani Peninsula.  3. Head to Northern Greece: - Visit Thessaloniki, Greece''s second largest city, with its vibrant food scene and Byzantine history. - Explore mountainous regions like Meteora, home to spectacular Eastern Orthodox monasteries. - Spend time in the scenic Pindus Mountains and Zagori region.  4. Consider mainland destinations: - Visit the stunning monasteries of Meteora in central Greece. - Explore the archaeological sites and hiking trails of Delphi. - Head to the coastal town of Nafpaktos on the Gulf of Corinth.  The advantage of these alternatives is you can avoid the extreme heat of Athens in late June, while still experiencing the history, culture, and natural beauty of Greece. The islands, mountains, and smaller towns may also be more comfortable and enjoyable for an active 7-year-old.  Let me know if you''d like me to elaborate on any of these Greece alternatives or if you have other ideas for your family trip!', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2024-04-15T13:29:09.096000'),
