(77901, '181602CA-556A-412A-8135-AC5188C1A973', 'Don''t worry, both Naxos and Crete have plenty of activities to keep an adventurous 7-year-old girl entertained! Here are some ideas for kid-friendly things to do on each island that align with her interests:  Naxos: - Beach time! Naxos has amazing beaches perfect for swimming, boogie boarding, and building sandcastles. Agios Prokopios, Agia Anna, and Plaka beaches are fantastic options.  - Visit Petres Aqua Park - This water park has slides, pools, and aquatic playgrounds.  - Take a boat tour to explore little islands and sea caves near Naxos. She may spot dolphins!  - Check out the Naxos Horse Farm to see horses and farm animals.  - Hike part of the Byzantine Trail for gorgeous views and the chance to see wildflowers and goats.  - Visit villages like Apiranthos to wander the marble paths and see traditional island life.  Crete:  - Cretaquarium in Heraklion - One of the best aquariums in Greece with sea turtles, sharks, and interactive exhibits.  - Matala Beach with caves and rocks to explore at the water''s edge.  - Take a boat tour along the coast from Rethymno to dolphin/sea turtle watch.  - Lassithi Plateau to see windmills and visit a petting zoo.  - Walk part of the Samaria Gorge for a bit of hiking adventure (only the initial part is stroller-friendly).  - Check out recreated Minoan houses at the Archaeological Site of Ancient Eleftherna.  You can also book kid-friendly experiences like pottery classes, cooking lessons, and farm visits through services like Airbnb. Having a rental car on Crete especially gives you flexibility.  With a mix of beaches, mild hikes, animal encounters, and local activities, your daughter is sure to have an amazing time on both islands! Let me know if you need any other specific recommendations.', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2024-04-18T22:09:08.320226'),
